         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">24 Augt. [18]94 ¶ Sir, ¶  ¶ I beg to request that you will be good enough to instruct Mr. Charles French Junr. of your office to wait upon the Inspector of Lunatic Asylums with a view of ascertaining ...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">94.08.24c</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">From Charles Topp</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">No.2781, p. 669, unit 104, VPRS 1187/P, outward registered correspondence, VA 475 Chief Secretary's Department, Public Record Office of Victoria.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: Geneva; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">24 Augt. [18]94<note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-family: Geneva; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <seg style="font-style: italic; ">editorial addition</seg>.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: Geneva; "
               xml:lang="en">Sir,</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: Geneva; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I beg to request that you will be good enough to instruct Mr. Charles French Junr. of your office to wait upon the Inspector of Lunatic Asylums with a view of ascertaining his fitness for the position of an Asylum Warder.<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-family: Geneva; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Charles H. French. See T. Wilson to M, 13 February 1894.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; font-family: Geneva; "
               xml:lang="en">I have the honor to be,</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; font-family: Geneva; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Sir,</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; font-family: Geneva; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Your most obedient servant,</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; font-family: Geneva; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Charles A. Topp</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; font-family: Geneva; "
               xml:lang="en">The Government Botanist</p>
